    "Asset managers invest pooled funds on behalf of clients, including mutual funds, pension funds, and investment advisors.",
    "They produce fund prospectuses, shareholder reports, investor letters, and market outlooks.",
    "Internally, they maintain investment committee memos, research reports, and risk reports.",
    "Public mutual fund documents and investor letters are available, whereas internal research and risk memos usually remain confidential.",
    "Hedge Funds & Private Investment Firms."
